Taiwan's statistical authority on Friday lowered its forecast for the island's 2019 economic growth to 2.19 percent. The latest growth forecast was 0.08 percentage points lower than the previous one made in February. The statistical agency expects Taiwan's per capita GDP in 2019 to reach 24,827 US dollars, and the consumer price index to rise 0.71 percent year on year. Many think tanks in Taiwan hold prudent views on the economic outlook of the island. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star